deck: A comic book series based on a 1954 family/adventure TV series The Adventures of Rin Tin Tin.

description:
There's a Menace meteor hurtling towards Beanotown... and it's heading straight for Dennis's house! Eek!

What else is happening in Beanotwon this week?

  • Escape Dennis's spikey hair!
  • Discover if you're allergic to homework!
  • Win a Kindle Fire HDX!

PLUS... all your comic strip favourites and all-new Menace missions!

Living Nightmares

Continuing the story of Nickolas Merrick, the Behemoth. In an encounter with an enigmatic stranger, Merrick seeks a return to normal, but receives anything but as he is thrust into battle with strange creatures and a sinister plot involving the mysterious woman, Lyla.
name: Living Nightmares

description:
Cicada: The Awakening

Old habits die hard... Unfortunately, old enemies not so much. Jack and Billy Blaze are blindsided by the old gang and it's up to Cicada to save the day. With the assistance of Tech and Master Chen's ancient healing techniques, Cicada is armed and ready to shock the world.
name: Cicada: The Awakening

description: What forces and events shape a man at war?

Introduced by your host, The Bloke, a Victorian undertaker, Bloke's Terrible Tomb of Terror is a homage to the classic horror anthology magazines that we grew up loving. This is an ongoing, self-published series. The third issue features six stories with a mix of retro and modern art styles.

Written by Jason 'The Bloke' Crawley & Mike Hoffman Artwork by Mike Hoffman & Rock Baker

Taste Test

It's the 100th anniversary of Brittleville! And it brings together the best and the worst of the town: bullies, goth kids, Candy Zombies and pie tasters!

But those who can't resist eating candy will be really sorry!

Echo and Chance finally spend some quality time together, and make important discoveries about Chance's past!
name: Taste Test

description: As powerful forces assemble upon Sela, Dianne makes a hard decision to send her away from Nova Cielo. But as usual, things don't go as planned for Sela, Robb, and Maya. Can the three of them find a way to get Sela off the island without winding up in prison or worse? Meanwhile, Captain Jenny Avery is baffled by the unexpected scrutiny she and her crew find themselves under and decides to make some inquiries of her own.

The Peddler's Hoard

The discovery of an impossible craft buried for over two centuries off the coast of Norfolk leads to a disastrous incursion into time, the release of ancient forces and a journey beyond the realm of reality.

In 1784 the Flint brothers are to discover their world is not what it seems...
name: Episode Two: The Peddler's Hoard

description:
Rise and Slime!

They're Back! And the GWASH MONSTERS Attack! Cray City is being threatened! OH NO! What's happening to the Monkey and the Duck! Does the Duck survive the Forrest of Slimy Trees? The Cray Mayor is concerned! Especially for... the Imploding Cray Button! Revisit the first self-published EPIC tale of award winning Famous Cartoonistcray ART BALTAZAR...before he was famous.
name: Rise and Slime!

description: After the massive magical explosion that ended the hurricane, Zoe, Liz, and Jasmine are lost at sea! The other cadets scramble to find them, but they’ve drifted into a strange cave full of Darkness Beasts. Zoe’s diamond is having a strange reaction to some of the murals in the cave—could they finally be learning the secrets of the Crystal Cadets?
The Damage Incorporated crew takes on the deadly Malcom McCrazy.

Storm

Having extracted the information they needed from the cybernetic mercenary, Snare, Gabe and his team prepare for an all out assault of a facility dealing in human trafficking.

Looking for answers as to who exactly is behind this operation, Gabe must fight his way through an army of mercenaries, mechs, and elite assassins.
name: Storm

description:
Chosen

Raven reels in the aftermath of her father's death and vows to find the real killer. Her investigation uncovers Eddie's secret life, a mysterious woman, a key without a lock, and a creature beyond imagination.
name: Chosen

description:
It's the giant-sized, senses shattering conclusion of the Terrible Fruit Bats! All-out monster mayhem is in full effect. with the fate of a small town at it's center! Will an empire of the undead rise? Or will Halloween Man save the day?!

Also in the issue, we dig up a moldy, oldie where our half-dead hero runs across the Devil himself! Plus, special features include a look at Hammer Horror from vampire novelist Jason Henderson and editor Russell Hillman's love note to 80's classic, "American Werewolf in London!"
name: The Terrible Fruit Bats Part Three

description:
Jesus takes the fight directly to Zeus and Isis, the two mythological gods leading a horde of desperate, worship-hungry deities! But do Jesus, Satan, and Sister Maria actually stand a chance? And can they keep their sh*t together long enough to stop the coming madness?

Back-up Feature:

  • Holy F*ck Origins: 506 AD + 1 BC

Release Dates:

  • Digital Edition - 2/18/2015
  • Print Edition - 4/15/2015

name: Keep F*cking

description:
The Contest

The cosmic battle continues on a contested planet between the Horsemen and their nemesis. A challenge of mind, body and soul will determine who rules... or will it?
name: The Contest

description:
Hell hath no fury like a woman scorned!

Set in a time when war was the sport of kings and supreme loyalty demanded supreme sacrifice. Adapted from an original screenplay, a re-imagining of the Old Testament account of King Ahab and Queen Jezebel.

Follow the epic tale of Jezebel's rise from reluctant queen to all-powerful sorceress - as she unleashes the gods of the underworld... in her quest for supremacy.
Our firefighter finds out he's part of a world he thought only existed in legends. But can this vampire lady help him figure out who he is before the agent sent to collect him does?

Green Achers

Now he's a father, Pewfell is more determined than ever to achieve success in his chosen career of wizardry, but somehow it continues to eluded him. When his perpetually pesky gnome tenant is apparently killed in the act of remodeling his house, it looks like a new opportunity might be about to open up for Pewfell in the country...
name: Green Achers

description:
As their new adventure begins, old faces appear. Now, Vesper must decide whether to forgive and forget, or to let the flames of revenge consume her, unaware that a much greater evil is just around the corner.

Note: The digital edition (2/18/2015) for this issue was released before the print edition.

Things have gone from bad to worse as our wayward teens are surrounded by the secret government organization that originally experimented on them. Both those that have been captured and those that continue to evade are in a no-holds-barred battle royal as the Supernals fight for freedom, while the organization fights for control.

Farewell to Childhood

Unagi is hunted down by his Mother's Killer, and during his escape discovers Tanuki Blade, a once mystical now shattered weapon. However, Tanuki Blade will not help Unagi enact revenge. Will Tanuki Blade deem Unagi worthy enough and help him find an alternative solution in his desperate struggle?
name: Farewell to Childhood

description: Anneli discovers a hidden secret from Devan's past as their relationship begins to bloom. Meanwhile, Maximus' son begins to regret the bargain he made to help depose his father.

Continue your journey to humanity's dark side, as Neil Gibson returns with a fourth volume of his best-selling series TWISTED DARK to chill and shock. It contains readers' favorite story so far - Little Piggy.
name: Volume Four

description: The X-Men struggle to deal with the death of one of their own - but before even a moment of silence can pass, the mysterious Mr. Sinister arrives, intent on giving the X-Men a lot more to mourn! Then, Gambit returns - but what does he want? The Fenris twins threaten to expose the Ragin' Cajun's past sins unless he obeys them. But with Rogue on the other side, to whom will Remy finally lend his loyalty? And what decision does Rogue make that will affect her budding relationship with Iceman? The X-Men soon discover that mutants are being hunted for sport on the island of Krakoa - but can they pull off the rescue of without becoming part of the game, or will malevolent media mogul Mojo make 'stars' of them all? Collecting ULTIMATE X-MEN (2001) #46-57.
name: Volume 5

description: Its Velda vs the Red Menace when our plucky 1950's sleuth uncovers a sinister Commie plot to take over America! Also in this issue: Velda takes on a double role to outwit kidnappers when she becomes "The Prisoner of Zendaville," and tracks a murderous art thief who can't resist "The Naked Milkmaid." An adventure of Neolithica: Girl of the Pleistocene and Hawkshaw Hawk: Bird Detective round out the issue.

Len's Story

Brand New Video Girl

Sweet guy Hiromu is so shy that wild horses couldn't drag him over to introduce himself to Ayumi, the beautiful new girl in his art class. But Video Girl Len is going to do her darnedest to help Hiromu find happiness with the girl of his dreams!

Sequel

Hiromu's one-track mind has always been focused on his dream of becoming a manga artist. So when his head is turned by the arrival of gorgeous new classmate Ayumi, Hiromu is totally unprepared to deal with his newfound romantic feelings. But with the help of his girl-crazy best friend Toshiki, his art teacher Mr. Moteuchi, and peppy Video Girl Len, maybe even bashful Hiromu can be lucky in love!
name: Len's Story

description:
Collects Ramayan 3392 AD: Reloaded #1-5:

A story thousands of years in the making, a re-imagining of one of the greatest tales ever, retold in the post-apocalyptic future. Mankind has been devastated and in its wake the monstrous being Ravan and his dark hordes threaten to wipe out what little is left of humanity but hope is alive in the form of mighty warrior Prince Ram. Along with his brother Lakshman and the lovely Seeta, daughter of Mother Earth, Rama sets out on a perilous journey to end Ravan's bloody grip on the world. Ramayan 3392 A.D. is an epic adventure which has been called "India's answer to Lord of the Rings" by the Times of India and features a surreal cast of fantastical creatures and spectacular battles, all within an astonishing quest to save humanity from a darker evil that the world has ever encountered before.
name: Volume 2: The Tome of the Wastelands

description:
Collects Ramayan 3392 AD: Reloaded #6-8:

A story thousands of years in the making, a re-imagining of one of the greatest tales ever, retold in a post-apocalyptic future. Rama, the prince of Armagar, was exiled from his home for surrendering the fort of Janasthan to Ravan's forces. During his exile Rama comes to become the protector of Seeta, the daughter of mother earth. After Seeta was kidnapped by the asura prime, Ravan, Rama wanders aimlessly for a year serving as a mercenary for the rebels of Kishkrida led by the exiled Vanara king Shugreave. However, when the mad Vanara king Baali unleashes the dreadful and unstoppable Mahabali upon Shugreave's rebels, Rama and Shugreave decide to take back the throne from Baali, the Monster King of Kishkinda! Ramayan 3392AD is an epic adventure that has been called 'India's answer to Lord of the Rings' by Times of India and features a surreal cast of fantastical creatures and spectacular battles, all within an astonishing quest to save humanity from darker evil than the world has ever encountered before.
name: Volume 3: In the Clutches of Baali - The Monster King

description: The first printed edition of the story previously available in Marvel's innovative Infinite Comics format! Peter Parker has just returned from being replaced by Dr. Octopus - so now it's time to eschew Ock's more villainous tendencies and return to a life of heroic virtue, right? Maybe not! Because suddenly, Peter has lost his memory. He doesn't know who he is - either as Peter or as Spider-Man. And he's robbing a bank! With Peter seemingly turned to a life of crime, what does this mean for the hero once known as the Amazing Spider-Man? Gear up for a Spider-Man epic unlike any other as the recently returned wall-crawler travels to a place you never thought possible: the criminal underworld! Collecting AMAZING SPIDER-MAN: WHO AM I? INFINITE COMIC #1-12.
name: HC

description:
Another World

Punk Rock & The End of the World...with Swords!

Katherine Brody, a singer in a punk band from Oregon is having trouble figuring out where she fits in the world, least of all where she fits in her widowed father, Ben's life. Now the world has been plunged in to darkness with no electricity or modern technology. What's a young punk going to do?
name: Another World, Part One

description: Two of Spider-Man's deadliest foes, Hobgoblin and Carnage, take center stage - as heroes! In the wake of AXIS, Roderick Kingsley, the original Hobgoblin, is back in the suit and back in New York with a new mission: to make YOU the best you can be! But when Phil Urich, the former Hobgoblin, tries to get rid of Kingsley for good, will the heroic Hobgoblin be forced to revert to his wicked ways? Meanwhile, if symbiotic serial killer Carnage has given up villainy, then why has he kidnapped one of New York City's most beloved news anchors? The Sin-Eater returns, with a surprising mission - and if all this isn't enough for Carnage to worry about, he's still on the authorities' most-wanted list! The effects of AXIS continue in this surprising saga - don't miss it! Collecting AXIS: HOBGOBLIN #1-3 and AXIS: CARNAGE #1-3.
name: TPB

description: It's the return of the New Warriors, drawn by superstar artist Skottie Young (ROCKET RACCOON)! When Night Thrasher strikes a mysterious deal with a reality-TV producer, the New Warriors move out of New York - and into a very cramped van - to travel across America, and help small-town residents deal with the roving villains and superhuman threats that the major super-teams are too busy to tackle! But will the Warriors' filmed exploits be uplifting, or just exploitative? And is heartland America ready for big-city super heroics? Find out as the Warriors take on Tiger Shark, the Armadillo, the Super-Apes, the Controller, the Mad Thinker's Intellectual Robots and more - and unknowingly set the stage for the superhuman Civil War! Plus: the sweeps-week debuts of Microbe and Debrii! Collecting NEW WARRIORS (2005) #1-6.
name: TPB

description: "So you've finally decided to come back to this country, Lily," Alex says in a cold tone. I think he still hasn't forgiven me... Eighteen months ago, Lily fell in love with the prince of the Sapphiros kingdom in the Diamond Isles. After a mysterious disappearance, she finally braves the criticism she faces and returns to the island to rescue her son, Michales, who was taken from her at birth and is poised to be the new heir to the kingdom. "This is all wrong-that baby belongs to Alex and me!"
name: Marrying His Majesty 1

description: There is something evil lurking in the woods along the Congaree River and it's not just Clem and his cousin Cletus...

ORIGINAL SIN tie-in! When Matt learns something about his past that's too terrible to accept, he seeks out his mother - only to find her in more trouble than he could possibly have imagined. Prepare for the untold story of how Matt Murdock's mother became Sister Maggie as her biggest sin is finally revealed! Then, Daredevil takes on a new case with a killer opposition - and faces the Purple Children! One of DD's oldest foes has unleashed a force that he can't fight without being swallowed by his darkest moods and thoughts. As the Purple Children steal everything Matt Murdock has achieved for himself, is this the beginning of a new, grim chapter in Daredevil's life? Plus: Celebrate Daredevil's fiftieth anniversary with a look at the future! Collecting DAREDEVIL (2014) #1.50 and #6-10.
name: Volume 2

description:
The Gunfighting Stranger

A lone gunslinger enters the corrupt town of Lynchburg hellbent on vengeance. Meanwhile, the dead are rising from their graves, hungry for the flesh of the living.
name: The Gunfighting Stranger

description: Set in the distant future of 2025. The main characters and future technologies are introduced. NASA launches a historic mission. Certain challenges and discoveries arise, as this epic story begins.

Love Harvey Kurtzman's original MAD? Then you will have to have Ross Andru and Mike Esposito's historic satire and parody magazine, Get Lost. Originally released in 1953, Get Lost delivered three groundbreaking, laugh-filled issues before Bill Gaines sued the magazine's distributor, shutting down production of the magazine. Even though Gaines lost the lawsuit, Andru and Esposito never produced more Get Lost. Hermes Press' historic reprint collects all three issues of the magazine on heavy coated matte paper together with an introductory essay by noted pop-culture historian Ron Goulart, an interview with Mike Esposito, and tons of documentary material in one volume. For this archival edition Hermes Press has painstakingly reconstructed Get Lost's artwork using the original black-and-white line art and recoloring it from scratch. Mike Esposito says it "looks better than the original." MAD's most noteworthy competitor is a treasure to behold for fans of Alfred E. Newman as well as comic book collectors, fans, and anyone looking for a good laugh.
name: TPB

description: Igor the Cat has obtained his 'place' among hundreds of comic cats. He is an example that the language of comics easily communicates with all cultures and generations. (Zoran Stefanovic)
Igor and Ignis start their training, the first mission: Find the legendary Bird of Fire!
name: In Search of the Bird of Fire

description:
Dark Horse Comics is proud to present a series of digital sampler comics, Builds Characters. Each sampler will focus on a single creator and excerpt variety of their past and upcoming works with Dark Horse.

Enjoy this free sampling from Harvey Award–winning writer and artist Matt Kindt, featuring a choice selection of the hotly anticipated Past Aways, as well as excerpts from modern classics MIND MGMT, The Complete Pistolwhip, and 3 Story!

Brace yourself for a delicious adventure, full of magic and action.

A journey through a simple man's fight to protect his recipe from the dark forces of a greedy, evil sorceress.

Gray Morrow's career spanned over forty years — he toiled as an illustrator, comic book storyteller, painter, creator of myths and tales, a ghost artist for others behind on their deadlines, and a comic strip artist. His talents were varied and he was consistently good in a profession where quantity was and is sometimes more important than quality. It's clear to anyone who takes the time to look at his body of work that he had point of view that was consistent, compelling, and good to look at. Orion, his homage to the epic “swashbuckler” newspaper strips of the 1930s and pulp sci-fi and fantasy, was published installments in Heavy Metal magazine in the 1970s, but has never been published in its entirety, until now. Read one of Morrow's favorite efforts which bristles with pulp sensabilites, engaging characters, and non-stop action. Also, Morrow's three comic book story arc, Edge of Chaos, his rumination on the Greek myths, is also assembled, for the first time as a complete story to compliment Orion.
name: TPB

description: Since the dawn of time, a secret war has been waged between two species, each determined to annihilate the other. Throughout the millennia, they have kept their battle confined to the shadows; however, one brazen act has escalated this conflict to a fever pitch. As the world careens toward Armageddon, every human on the planet will soon be forced to CHOOSE A SIDE!
name: Volume One

description: Millie falls passionately in love with Greek banker Leandro, but soon after they get married she catches him having an affair with her own sister, Becca. It's been one year since Millie left him that day, and she resolves to return to Leandro to take the orphan of her now-dead sister from him. Even so, Millie still loves Leandro. Nothing could change her feelings toward him. But when she arrives, she sees a half-naked woman in the arms of her half-naked husband...
name: Twin Bride 1

description: Up-and-coming interior designer Lucinda is dumped by her fiance and develops a mistrust of men. When she gets a job offer to renovate a luxurious mansion on the island of Saint Lucia in the Caribbean Sea, it's a dream come true! But there's a problem with her employer. It's Zane Alexander-a man for whom she once had feelings! He's the last person in the world she wants to be around right now. But as soon as they arrive at the island, he invites her to spend her time there as a vacation...with him.
name: Vol. 1

description: Hermes Press adds yet another important title to its line-up of classic comic book and comic strip reprints with Roy Rogers King of the Cowboys: The Collected Dailies and Sundays. During the 1950s Roy Rogers King of the Cowboys was one of the most widely read newspaper comic strips in America. Now for the first time Hermes Press presents an in-depth collection of this important feature which surveys the greatest cowboy series to grace news­papers. See the adventures of Roy Rogers, Dale Evans, and Trigger in both black-and-white daily strips and four complete full color continuities of the Sundays. Highlighting this collection is a comprehensive sampling of Silver Age master Alex Toth's artwork on the title. Other artists featured in this survey of the Roy Rogers daily and Sunday strips are Mike Arens, and Tom, Chuck, and Bob McKimson.
name: HC

volume.name: Roy Rogers, King of the Cowboys: The Collected Dailies and Sundays

description:
Curse of the Dreadnuts 1

The Samurai-Astronauts of 2 different eras encounter a foe like they never met before... The Dreadnuts. Evil zombie pirates bent on world destruction. Can Al, the immortal leader of the Samurnauts lead his students to victory over an enemy more powerful than they ever faced before? And how did the Dreadnuts survive to return for revenge? There's only one way to find out!
name: The Curse of the Dreadnuts

description: A young temptress, who deceives elderly men, is desperate to avoid falling victim to the same trap she has set. When Celia senses someone's presence and turns around, she finds Luke gazing intently at her. Luke is the son of her mother's lover, Lionel. What is he doing here? Does he want to condemn her? She didn't approve of the affair, but she isn't about to let Luke meet with her mother, who is still heartbroken by Lionel's recent death. On impulse, Celia misleads Luke to believe that she is his father's mistress while desperately trying not to get swayed by Luke's seductive charms.
name: Secret Passions I

description: Thief. Goddess. Headmistress. Queen. The X-Man called Storm has always defied a single title. And her desire to better the world has never been limited to only her own kind. On an ongoing mission to foster goodwill, and safeguard both mankind and mutants, Ororo Munroe will travel the globe - confronting villains, gods, monsters and everything in between. She will overthrow tyrants, quell tsunamis and strive to see her dream for the world realized. She is Storm, a hero like no other - and the skies will tremble at the sight of their namesake. But now, Storm must handle the fallout caused by familiar faces from her past. Why is Callisto kidnapping wayward youths from the streets of New York? Will Storm's romance with Forge be reignited? And can Yukio help Storm deal with the death of Wolverine? Collecting STORM (2014) #1-5.
name: Volume 1

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: It's back, the comic book adaptation of one of Irwin Allen's most fondly remembered sci-fi television shows of the 1960s: The Time Tunnel. This volume contains both of Gold Key comics' issues of The Time Tunnel and supplementary essays, photos, and more! Go back in time to the 1960s and The Time Tunnel.
name: TPB

volume.name: The Time Tunnel: The Complete Series

description:
Dave and the Giant Pickle

VeggieTales Super Comics brings all the zaniest and fun you've come to expect in a popular new format. This comic includes the story, Dave and The Giant Pickle.

volume.name: VeggieTales SuperComics: Dave and the Giant Pickle

description: After her father's death, Darcy needs the inheritance that her godparent left her in order to pay off the family's debt. However, in order for her to receive the inheritance, she must get married within a year. As a last resort, she places an ad in the newspaper and advertises for a temporary husband. She believes the problem is solved until she discovers that the man who answered her ad was a lover from three years ago. And he wishes to take revenge on her?!
name: Vol. 1

description: It's back, the comic book adaptation of one of the most famous and popular sci-fi television series of the 1960s: Irwin Allen's Voyage to the Bottom of Sea. The first of two hardcover volumes presenting reprints of the entire series of Gold Key comic books featuring Admiral Nelson, Captain Crane, and the Seaview. Featuring painted cover art by George Wilson with interior artwork by such Silver Age greats as Mike Sekowsky, George Tuska, Don Heck, and Alberto Giolitti.
name: Volume One

volume.name: Voyage to the Bottom of the Sea: The Complete Series

description: It's a new mission for the first all-female team of X-Men! When the Shi'ar warrior Deathbird lands on S.W.O.R.D.'s doorstep at the brink of death, Abigail Brand calls the X-Men to investigate! But are even they equipped to handle this horrific new alien threat? As 'Genespliced' monstrosities engineered from the fiercest alien races across the galaxy threaten S.W.O.R.D.'s orbital base, the X-Men find themselves entangled in a conspiracy that connects to the assassination of Rachel Grey's family! Can the X-Men hope to stop an alien horde? Does Brand know more about the Genespliced than she's revealing? How does Rachel's uncle Vulcan tie in? And will Rachel forsake her teammates and risk Earth's safety to take revenge on those responsible for her family's deaths? Collecting X-MEN (2013) #18-22.
name: Volume 4

description: Your first look at Black Hood #1 is here! Get a sneak peek at the beginning of the NEW ONGOING SERIES from the brand new Dark Circle imprint. “The Bullet’s Kiss – Part 1 of 5” When Philadelphia police officer Greg Hettinger stepped into the middle of a gunfight, hot lead shredded his face—and he pulled the trigger, blind. Now Greg is waking up in a world where he’s a killer, hopelessly scarred and hooked on painkillers. What does a man do when he can no longer face the world, yet still wants to do good? He puts on a hood…
name: The Bullet's Kiss Chapter One

description: The saga of HISTORY's Vikings continues with this special one-shot! In the quiet moments after Ragnar hosts a feast, Floki entertains the guests with one of his favorite Norse legends. He tells a tale of Thor, who loses his famed hammer to the dreaded Frost Giants. When Odin refuses to help, Thor must turn to Loki and his unconventional means for assistance. For more, watch Vikings on HISTORY® Thursdays 10/9c.

Duck and cover, Archie’s heading to Chemistry class! Archie’s a pretty average student, except when it comes to working in the laboratory—in there, he’s a pretty average warhead! Luckily, he’s got Dilton and his friends to keep him from blowing up. Check out this collection of scientific stories and let’s hope the only lab Archie visits from now on is his dog Vegas!
